OVERVIEW: List build settings for project or target

List build settings with various filtering options. Without --target, shows
project-level settings.

Examples:
  xcodeproj-cli list-build-settings
  xcodeproj-cli list-build-settings --target MyApp
  xcodeproj-cli list-build-settings --target MyApp --config Debug
  xcodeproj-cli list-build-settings -t MyApp -c Release --json
  xcodeproj-cli list-build-settings --all --show-inherited

Notes:
  - Without --target, shows project-level settings
  - Without --config, shows all configurations
  - JSON output is useful for automated processing

USAGE: xcodeproj-cli list-build-settings [--project <project>] [--workspace <workspace>] [--verbose] [--dry-run] [--target <target>] [--config <config>] [--show-inherited] [--json] [--all]

OPTIONS:
  -p, --project <project> Path to .xcodeproj file (default: looks for
                          *.xcodeproj in current directory)
  -w, --workspace <workspace>
                          Path to .xcworkspace file
  -V, --verbose           Enable verbose output with performance metrics
  --dry-run               Preview changes without saving
  -t, --target <target>   Target name (optional, shows project settings if
                          omitted)
  -c, --config <config>   Configuration name (optional, shows all if omitted)
  -i, --show-inherited    Show inherited settings from project
  -j, --json              Output in JSON format
  -a, --all               Show all settings including default values
  --version               Show the version.
  -h, --help              Show help information.

